<HEADLINE>
<P>
LAPD 'COPSPEAK' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Re "LAPD Lingo," Dec. 19: 
</P>
<P>
 Not only is duis pronounced deuce it is also spelled deuce. This term comes 
from a shortening of the former Vehicle Code section, "502," which stated the 
offense of driving under the influence from 1935 until 1959. (The offense is 
presently stated in Vehicle Code section 23152.) As in a game of cards, the two 
becomes a deuce. "DUI" is simply the abbreviation for "driving under the 
influence." 
</P>
<P>
 THOMAS R. KRAG 
</P>
<P>
 Arcadia 
</P>
</TEXT>
