 In a poll of Associated Press subscribers in more than 30 countries in Europe, 
the Middle East, Asia, Oceania, Africa and South America, Brazil accounted for 
the top two sports stories of the year. Brazil's World Cup soccer victory was 
voted the No. 1 story, followed by the death of Brazilian Formula One driver 
