VENTURA COUNTY ROUNDUP: MONEY STORE OPENS OFFICE IN OXNARD'S FINANCIAL PLAZA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Jack Searles 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Money Store Investment Corp. has opened an office in Oxnard's Financial 
Plaza.The unit will offer Small Business Administration-guaranteed loans to 
companies in Ventura, Santa Barbara and San Luis Obispo counties. 
</P>
<P>
 The nationwide Money Store chain says it issued $319 million in SBA-backed 
loans in 1993. Long-term financing of up to $2.5 million is available for real 
estate purchases, construction, equipment and other purposes. 
</P>
<P>
 David Mellman, formerly a loan officer with company's Encino office, has been 
named to head the Ventura operation. Before joining the Money Store, he was a 
bond underwriter for Reliance Surety Co., serving contractors and developers in 
Ventura and Santa Barbara counties. 
</P>
