<HEADLINE>
<P>
YOUTH CLUB BOARD ELECTS NEW PRESIDENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PAUL ELIAS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Mel Sheeler has been elected president of the 15-member board of directors of 
the Boys & Girls Club of Ventura. 
</P>
<P>
 The 52-year-old Sheeler, a Ventura County native, belonged to the club as a 
child. 
</P>
<P>
 "I was in it before it was called the Boys & Girls Club," he said. 
</P>
<P>
 The nonprofit club serves more than 2,500 county children a year, many of them 
from disadvantaged homes. It offers activities, homework areas, game rooms, 
leadership clubs, music lessons, drama performances, arts and crafts and field 
trips. 
</P>
<P>
 Sheeler is general manager of Hilford Moving & Storage in Ventura. He was 
president of the Ventura Chamber of Commerce in 1992 and is a past-president of 
the East Ventura Kiwanis Club. PAUL ELIAS 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Appointment 
</P>
</TYPE>
