<HEADLINE>
<P>
CHP ARRESTS 21 IN COUNTY IN DRUNK DRIVING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MATTHEW MOSK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Drunk driving arrests over the Christmas weekend were down slightly from 
previous years, the California Highway Patrol reported Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 During a maximum-enforcement period from 6 p.m. Friday to 6 a.m. Monday, 21 
people in Ventura County were arrested on suspicion of driving under the 
influence of alcohol, the Highway Patrol reported. 
</P>
<P>
 During a similar period in 1992, there were 24 arrests, and in 1990, there 
were 43 arrests. Last year's figures were not available Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 Accidents attributed to drunk drivers were also down this year, with only two 
minor accidents reported through Monday. During the holiday weekend in 1990 two 
people were killed in accidents involving alcohol. MATTHEW MOSK 
</P>
