<P>
OAKLEY WILL UNDERGO TOE SURGERY TODAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Forward Charles Oakley will undergo surgery today for a partially dislocated 
toe, sidelining him for at least six weeks, the New York Knicks said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 Oakley decided on surgery Sunday night after the Knicks lost their fifth game 
in a row, 107-104, to the Bulls at Chicago.He had tried playing with a special 
shoe but it didn't help. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's just too much," he said. "I really can't get any lift. I might as well 
do it now so it doesn't affect the whole year. . . . We're just wasting time." 
</P>
<P>
 The injury is to the second toe on Oakley's right foot, and the special shoe 
caused him to sprain his ankle slightly several times after he returned to the 
lineup Thursday, Oakley said. 
</P>
