<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOYS' BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; TROY, TORRES WORK OVERTIME TO DEFEAT COMPTON 
CENTENNIAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jon Torres made eight free throws in overtime to help Troy to a 73-63 victory 
over Compton Centennial in the first round of the Brea Olinda tournament Monday 
at Brea. 
</P>
<P>
 Torres made a three-point basket to tie score with 10 seconds left in 
regulation. He finished with 16 points and eight assists for Troy (7-5). Jeff 
Sand added 24 points for the Warriors. 
</P>
<P>
 Paul Sykes has 23 points to lead Centennial. 
</P>
<P>
 In other Brea Olinda tournament games: 
</P>
<P>
 La Habra 87, La Canada St. Francis 65 -- Justin Marshall made seven 
three-pointers in the victory for La Habra (6-5). Teammates Dan Ploog and Corey 
Holbert each added 18. 
</P>
<P>
 Brea Olinda 72, Rancho Alamitos 60 -- Matt Bodiford scored 17 points and Shawn 
Collier scored 15 for Brea Olinda (9-3). The Wildcats play Norwalk Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Reebok Above the Rim tournament in Encinitas: 
</P>
<P>
 Mater Dei 75, San Diego Scripps Ranch 63 -- Schea Cotton had 23 points and 12 
rebounds and Clay McKnight had 21 points, including five three-pointers for 
Mater Dei, top-ranked in Orange County. 
</P>
<P>
 After leading, 32-31, at halftime, the Monarchs (12-1) outscored Scripps 
Ranch, 22-12, in the third quarter to take command. Scott Charity had 27 points 
for Scripps Ranch (10-1). 
</P>
<P>
 Mater Dei plays Anchorage Service at 6 p.m. tonight. 
</P>
<P>
 Ocean View 62, Bonanza (Nevada) 59 -- Dan McDonald scored 29 points and had 
nine rebounds for Ocean View (7-5). Erik Petersen had 13 points for the 
Seahawks, who played a first-round game Monday morning. 
</P>
<P>
 Ocean View also played Monday night and lost to Riverside North, 64-56. 
McDonald scored a game-high 22 points and seven rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
 Encinitas San Dieguito 70, Newport Harbor 60 -- Will Ranking scored 15 points 
for Newport Harbor in first-round action. San Dieguito's Pat Conahan was the 
high-scorer with 26 points. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Canyon tournament: 
</P>
<P>
 Cerritos 76, Saddleback 50 -- Nick Maddox 41 points and made 13 of 13 free 
throws to lead Cerritos to the victory in the first-round game. 
</P>
<P>
 Bobby Dreyer had 13 points for Saddleback (2-9), which plays Magnolia in a 
consolation game today at 4:40 p.m. Cerritos plays El Dorado Wednesday at 3 
p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 El Dorado 71, Magnolia 41 -- Dan Simonsen had 16 points and Dustin Miller 
added 15 for El Dorado (9-2), which outscored Magnolia, 34-18, in the first 
half. Ahmad Shurdim had 14 points for Magnolia (6-6). 
