<P>
THE BOWLS DAILY REPORT; FIESTA; INJURY SIDELINES NOTRE DAME'S KINDER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Crippled by injuries at tailback all season, Notre Dame was stung again when 
sophomore Randy Kinder, the team's leading rusher, was declared out of the 
Fiesta Bowl against Colorado because of an injured right knee. 
</P>
<P>
 Kinder, who started five games and led the Irish with 702 yards, was hurt in 
the final minutes of a 2 1/2-hour practice Monday. 
