<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE BOWLS DAILY REPORT; ORANGE; SEAHAWK QUESTIONS SILENCE ERICKSON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Miami Coach Dennis Erickson walked out of an interview after practice when 
asked about the Seattle Seahawks' coaching job. 
</P>
<P>
 Erickson, preparing the No. 3 Hurricanes for Sunday's Orange Bowl against No. 
1 Nebraska, has been mentioned regarding NFL coaching jobs in Seattle, Denver 
and expansion Carolina. 
</P>
<P>
 When asked about Tom Flores' likely ouster as the Seahawks' coach, Erickson 
walked away from reporters without a word. Flores, coming off a 6-10 season, is 
to have his future in Seattle determined this week when he meets with team 
owner Ken Behring. 
</P>
<P>
 In November, Erickson said he would entertain NFL offers. In the last two 
weeks, the former Washington State coach has been rumored as the front-runner 
to replace Flores. 
</P>
<P>
 The Hurricanes are 63-8, including two national championships, in Erickson's 
six years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
