<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROYAL'S SMITH OPTS TO PLAY FOOTBALL FOR WASHINGTON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF FLETCHER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jermaine Smith, an All-Ventura County defensive back from Royal High, said 
Monday he will sign a letter of intent to play football at Washington. 
</P>
<P>
 Smith (6-feet, 180 pounds) visited Washington and Arizona State.He canceled 
trips to UCLA, Nevada Las Vegas and Colorado State after picking the Huskies. 
</P>
<P>
 "I like how (Washington) plays its defense," he said. "It's a lot of man to 
man, and that's what I like playing the best. They have a good wining program 
and they made a lot of trips to the Rose Bowl." 
</P>
<P>
 Smith, an All-Marmonte League selection, had one interception and nine pass 
deflections this season.  
</P>
<P>
 He is the third Royal player to make a college commitment. Besides Smith, 
center Steve Zirnite (Fresno State) and fullback Mike Reddington (Navy), 
tailback Jerome Lee is also expected to sign a letter of intent during the NCAA 
football signing period in February. JEFF FLETCHER 
</P>
</TEXT>
