<HEADLINE>
<P>
TIDBITS; NUTRITIOUS DINING FOR SINGLE APPETITES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By THE WASHINGTON POST 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 You eat a light lunch and get home late from work. You're tired and famished, 
so you grab dinner -- cheese, crackers and a couple of glasses of wine.And 
since you live alone and nobody's looking . . . well, what the heck, why not 
polish off the pint of Cherry Garcia? 
</P>
<P>
 Many people who live by themselves find it difficult to shop, cook and pay 
attention to good nutrition. As a result, they have the tendency to overeat. 
Here are some quick tips for healthier eating: 
</P>
<P>
 * Plan ahead. Do a weekly shopping trip. 
</P>
<P>
 * Have a snack late in the afternoon. If you eat lunch between noon and 1:30, 
no wonder you're starving by dinner time. Eat a piece of fruit just before you 
leave work. Then you won't walk in the house hungry enough to eat the rugs. 
</P>
<P>
 * Control portions of carryout and delivery food. Out of sight, out of mind. 
Before you eat the whole pizza, freeze half of it. 
</P>
<P>
 * Explore foods that are perfect for one serving. 
</P>
<P>
 * Eat breakfast for dinner. There's nothing wrong with having cereal and fruit 
for dinner. 
</P>
</TEXT>
