<HEADLINE>
<P>
CHRIS FOSTER: PLEASE DIAL 1-800 O.C. ALL-SPORTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRIS FOSTER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Hi, and welcome back to All Orange County Prep Sports Radio. That's all 
sports, all preps, all Orange County, all the time. 
</P>
<P>
 Let's go back to the phones. 
</P>
<P>
 Why is Tustin's basketball team so much better this season?  
</P>
<P>
 Well, basically, the Tillers have learned how to catch Doug Gottlieb's crisp 
passes. Not only has it provided more victories, but it has also cut down on 
team dental bills and kept Coach Andy Ground from looking into Rogaine with 
minoxidil. 
</P>
<P>
 Will the success of the World Cup help high school soccer?  
</P>
<P>
 Nope, sorry. Too many American sports fans still can't think with, or on, 
their feet. 
</P>
<P>
 Why did Brea Olinda change its name from Brea-Olinda?  
</P>
<P>
 It was former Ladycat basketball Coach Mark Trakh's last wish before he died 
of obscurity at Pepperdine. 
</P>
<P>
 Does Mater Dei's second-place finish at the Reebok Holiday Prep Classic mean 
the Monarchs are the second best high school team in the nation?  
</P>
<P>
 Don't know. The next poll won't be out until after the Nike shareholder 
meeting in San Diego. 
</P>
<P>
 Which was the most serious injury suffered on the Santa Ana Valley boys' 
basketball team?  
</P>
<P>
 Easy, that bruised ego. The Falcons cleared out space in the trophy case, then 
the season actually began. But don't worry, that room will be put to good use. 
I hear the school's soccer team is pretty good. 
</P>
<P>
 Hi, I have a question about high school golf.  
</P>
<P>
 Sorry kid, this is a sports show. Next. 
</P>
<P>
 You know Melody Peterson and the rest of the Mater Dei girls' basketball team 
are doing pretty good. So how come we don't hear more about them on your show?  
</P>
<P>
 Mater Dei has a girls' basketball team? Wow. 
</P>
<P>
 Who is the best basketball player in Orange County?  
</P>
<P>
 Gottlieb. 
</P>
<P>
 How about when the Clippers play at The Pond of Anaheim?  
</P>
<P>
 Oh, that's different. It's still Gottlieb, but it's a lot more crowded toward 
the bottom. 
</P>
<P>
 Who's the most self-sacrificing figure on the Orange County sports scene?  
</P>
<P>
 Why that would be referee Al Hackney, who went all the way to Las Vegas just 
to work in the Holiday Prep Classic. Apparently there must have been some 
shortage of refs in the greater Las Vegas area. He worked six games, all 
involving Mater Dei. He canceled his plans to return early so he could work the 
title game. The man's a giver. 
</P>
<P>
 If the Rams stay in Anaheim, will there still be a rain clause for high school 
games?  
</P>
<P>
 Yes. If it rains on the weekend of the Mater Dei-Los Alamitos playoff game, 
then the Rams have to move their game to Cerritos College. 
</P>
<P>
 The Brea Olinda girls' basketball team has had three coaches in three seasons 
and continues to win. Do the Ladycats actually need a coach?  
</P>
<P>
 No, but they could use a hyphen. 
</P>
<P>
 Now that Katella boys' basketball Coach Tom Danley has another decent team, 
will he give up his quest for an Orange County Section?  
</P>
<P>
 No. But considering the county's financial problems, Tom may have to reduce 
his goal. How about an Anaheim Section? 
</P>
<P>
 What game at The Pond will be the most exciting this season?  
</P>
<P>
 Mater Dei-Crenshaw Round III. That is, of course, provided the Clippers don't 
move any playoff games there. 
</P>
<P>
 Do you really dislike Mater Dei?  
</P>
<P>
 No, no, no. That would be silly. You can't harbor ill feelings toward a 
collection of buildings. 
</P>
<P>
 Well, that's all the time we have today. See ya next year. 
</P>
