</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Allen Krist 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Margarita, Junior 
</P>
<P>
 Basketball/Center 
</P>
<P>
 Last season, his first on the varsity, Krist started an occasional game for 
the Eagles. This year, after hitting the weight room hard in the off-season, 
Krist is helping lead the team.Last week, he averaged 16.7 points and 10 
rebounds as Santa Margarita won the Encinitas San Dieguito tournament for the 
second consecutive season. Krist, the tournament's most valuable player, had 15 
points and 14 rebounds in a 43-35 victory over Torrey Pines in the title game. 
In a 62-56 victory over San Diego St. Augustine in a semifinal, Krist, 6 feet 
8, had 14 points and 10 rebounds and played tough defense on Jelani McCoy, a 
6-10 center who has signed with UCLA. McCoy scored 23 points but had only six 
rebounds. "(Krist) has really improved offensively and defensively," Santa 
Margarita Coach Jerry DeBusk said. "He now has the physicalness it takes to get 
it done." Basketball 
