<P>
 Japan May File Charges in Bid-Rigging Cases: Japan's anti-monopoly watchdog is 
poised to file rare criminal charges against nine electronics firms and their 
executives, alleging bid-rigging going back as far as January, Japanese media 
said.The Fair Trade Commission has been investigating suspicions that the 
firms, which include industry leaders, repeatedly rigged bids and arranged in 
advance the winners of contracts for water supply and sewage systems for 
regional governments. A commission spokesman declined to comment on the 
reports. The five largest firms allegedly involved are Toshiba, Hitachi, 
Mitsubishi Electric, Fuji Electric and Meidensha. 
</P>
