COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: MISSION VIEJO; SCHOOL COMPUTER DONATIONS SOUGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF BEAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The deadline for the donate-a-computer drive at Capistrano Valley High School 
has been extended until March. 
</P>
<P>
 During the Computers for Schools Program, Pacific Bell, GTE, Bank of America 
and other large corporations will give Capistrano Valley High School 
refurbished computers for every used one donated to the school by companies 
with fewer than 200 employees. 
</P>
<P>
 Donated computers must be in working order for academic use and have a hard 
drive, monitor and keyboard. 
</P>
<P>
 The school needs at the minimum "286" IBM-style personal computers or similar 
Apple and Macintosh brands. 
</P>
<P>
 Additional computer peripherals and education software are also needed. 
</P>
<P>
 Companies with fewer than 200 employees that are upgrading their computer 
systems are encouraged to participate in the program. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call the school at (714) 364-6100 or fax a message, 
(714) 347-0514. JEFF BEAN 
</P>
