<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: TRABUCO CANYON; SOME IN PORTOLA HILLS GET WATER RATE HIKE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF BEAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Water rates will go up 15% Sunday for more than 500 homes in Portola Hills 
that are served by the Trabuco Canyon Water District. 
</P>
<P>
 The rate change is higher than a 5% increase for the rest of the district's 
2,600 customers, but Portola Hills residents will still have the lowest rates 
in the district, said district Treasurer Hershal Skidmore. 
</P>
<P>
 "This is to bring them a little closer," Skidmore said. 
</P>
<P>
 Both rate increases were approved by the board of directors last June when 
they adopted a 1994-95 budget, Skidmore said. 
</P>
<P>
 The 15% increase for Portola Hills residents was necessary because state 
officials have taken away property tax revenue that helped underwrite the cost 
of providing water to customers there, Skidmore said. JEFF BEAN 
</P>
