<HEADLINE>
<P>
GIRL, 17, FATALLY SHOT; YOUTH SOUGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Pomona police continued to search late Monday for a teen-age boy wanted for 
questioning in connection with the death of a 17-year-old girl who was shot 
while spending Christmas night at a friend's house.  
</P>
<P>
 Pomona Police Lt. Larry Todd identified the victim as Mary Price of 
Pomona.Todd described the boy being sought by police as a 15- to 17-year-old 
Pomona resident who was an acquaintance of the victim. 
</P>
<P>
 The victim's 14-year-old friend initially told investigators that they were 
alone in the home and that she did not know how the shooting occurred. But she 
later said a young man was visiting at the time of the incident, Pomona Police 
Lt. Louie Hernandez said. 
</P>
<P>
 Hernandez said it is unclear whether the young man was invited to the house. 
He had fled by the time police arrived, and it had not been determined whether 
he was responsible for the shooting or was merely a witness, Hernandez said. 
</P>
<P>
 Police have not determined a motive for the shooting. 
</P>
<P>
 The younger girl, who has not been identified because of her age, called 
police about 9:30 p.m. Sunday, saying her friend had been shot in the head. 
Price had been spending the night, and her friend's parents had left the girls 
alone while they went to a party, Hernandez said. 
</P>
