<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: HUNTINGTON BEACH; COUNCIL APPROVES FEE HIKES AT CITY 
STABLES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Equestrians who board their horses at the city's Central Park stables will pay 
higher fees starting in January. 
</P>
<P>
 The City Council recently approved a fee increase, despite objections from 
horse owners who believe the hike is unwarranted. 
</P>
<P>
 The new boarding rates include a $20 increase to $340 a month for a 
12-by-12-foot box stall with a tack locker, and a $15 increase to $240 a month 
for a 12-by-24-foot pipe corral with a tack locker. 
</P>
<P>
 Other increases include: a new $35 fee for trailer parking; a $35 increase to 
$280 for a 24-by-24-foot pipe corral, and a $30 increase to $450 to keep a 
horse in the show barn. 
</P>
<P>
 City officials said there has not been a fee increase in boarding prices since 
January, 1992. 
</P>
<P>
 The operator of Huntington Central Park Equestrian Center requested the fee 
increase because of increased costs of running the facility, including higher 
costs for hay and shavings. 
</P>
</TEXT>
