<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: RETAIL AND RESTAURANTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Greg Johnson, Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 CKE Tries Picante Grill: CKE Restaurants Inc., parent company of the Carl's 
Jr. chain, also is looking to the future with Picante Grill, a Mexican-style 
fast-food restaurant. 
</P>
<P>
 The first Picante Grill opened recently inside a Carl's Jr. restaurant in 
Orange. The location offers both Carl's Jr. regular fare and Mexican-style fast 
food. 
</P>
<P>
 The company, based in Anaheim, hasn't said yet how many of the dual-use 
restaurants it will open. 
</P>
