<HEADLINE>
<P>
5.5 QUAKE ROCKS ALEUTIANS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A magnitude 5.5 earthquake shook the Unimak region of the Aleutian islands on 
Sunday, scientists said. The National Earthquake Information Center said the 
quake occurred about 80 miles east of Dutch Harbor in the Aleutian Islands at 
7:08 p.m. PST Sunday. 
</P>
