<HEADLINE>
<P>
LARGE, BRIGHT OBJECT REPORTED SHOOTING ACROSS CALIFORNIA SKY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 People across Southern California and as far away as Reno called news media 
organizations, fire stations and astronomers to report that they saw a large 
object shoot across the night sky Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 "We've gotten calls since about 8:30 tonight and basically we believe it was a 
meteor," said Griffith Observatory guide Joel Harris. "It's not that unusual, 
but since people reported seeing it from far places we think it might have been 
bigger than most." 
</P>
<P>
 Callers from Sacramento, Riverside, Bakersfield and Reno described the 
shooting object as a big, bright light with a green, white or red tail. 
</P>
</TEXT>
