<HEADLINE>
<P>
FOR THE RECORD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Robert L. Citron -- Orange County Counsel Terry A. Andrus said that he did not 
cite a growing "pattern of deception and misrepresentation" in a draft letter 
that would have rejected payment of legal fees for former Treasurer-Tax 
Collector Robert L. Citron.A Times story on Sunday said that language was in a 
draft that was never sent. Knowledgeable sources, however, said that such 
language was used in discussions by the county counsel before a draft was 
written. Andrus said the draft letter focused on whether paying for Citron's 
defense would create a conflict of interest for the county. The county still 
has not decided whether to pay Citron's legal fees. 
</P>
